This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to extract fine-grained common-sense knowledge from user-generated content on social media. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also discusses different methods for learning contingency relations, which involves statistical modeling and optimization techniques, making it relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions information extraction, question answering, and text summarization, which are related to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
